813
01:10:49,235 --> 01:10:50,714
What are you doing?

814
01:10:51,035 --> 01:10:52,434
I'm spending time with you.

815
01:10:55,195 --> 01:10:56,548
Will you marry me?

816
01:10:57,555 --> 01:10:59,352
We can finally get up to Tahoe.

817
01:10:59,675 --> 01:11:01,074
Get married on the Nevada side...

818
01:11:01,395 --> 01:11:03,351
...honeymoon and be back
before we miss a case.

819
01:11:05,515 --> 01:11:07,904
What do you want me to do?
Get down on my knees?

820
01:11:08,555 --> 01:11:09,749
What do you want me to say?

821
01:11:10,715 --> 01:11:12,307
We belong together.

822
01:11:12,875 --> 01:11:14,467
We're the same species.

823
01:11:20,795 --> 01:11:24,105
I'm not very good at matters
of the heart. I mean...

824
01:11:24,715 --> 01:11:26,387
...the proverbial heart.

825
01:11:29,555 --> 01:11:30,988
Please be my wife.

826
01:11:35,355 --> 01:11:36,470
Just think about it.

827
01:11:51,555 --> 01:11:52,670
Breathe in.

828
01:11:56,475 --> 01:11:57,510
Breathe in.

829
01:12:10,515 --> 01:12:11,550
I'm good.

830
01:12:19,155 --> 01:12:23,626
I don't understand a God who would let
us meet, if we could never be together.

831
01:12:27,115 --> 01:12:28,104
He didn't tell you.

832
01:12:32,195 --> 01:12:33,105
Tell me what?

833
01:12:33,755 --> 01:12:34,983
Maybe you should ask him.

834
01:12:35,715 --> 01:12:37,353
No, I'm asking you.

835
01:12:48,395 --> 01:12:50,067
Seth knows no fear...

836
01:12:50,395 --> 01:12:51,589
...no pain...

837
01:12:51,875 --> 01:12:53,354
...no hunger.

838
01:12:54,475 --> 01:12:56,750
He hears music in the sunrise.

839
01:12:58,995 --> 01:13:00,713
But he'd give it all up.

840
01:13:00,995 --> 01:13:02,428
He loves you that much.

841
01:13:05,075 --> 01:13:06,713
I don't understand.

842
01:13:09,675 --> 01:13:11,108
He can fall.

843
01:13:11,755 --> 01:13:14,315
He can give up his existence
as he knows it.

844
01:13:14,595 --> 01:13:17,507
He can give up eternity and become...

845
01:13:17,795 --> 01:13:18,910
...one of us.

846
01:13:19,715 --> 01:13:20,989
It's up to you.

847
01:13:22,875 --> 01:13:24,388
How do you know this?

848
01:13:30,075 --> 01:13:31,588
Because I did it.

849
01:14:07,595 --> 01:14:09,426
Seth, I need to talk to you.

850
01:14:13,715 --> 01:14:15,546
Seth, please.

851
01:14:18,515 --> 01:14:19,504
Please be here.

852
01:14:21,795 --> 01:14:23,626
God, help me through this.

853
01:14:34,555 --> 01:14:36,113
You are so beautiful.

854
01:14:38,755 --> 01:14:40,427
You'll always be that way.

855
01:14:43,835 --> 01:14:45,632
Jordan asked me to go away with him...

856
01:14:45,915 --> 01:14:47,234
...and get married.

857
01:14:49,995 --> 01:14:51,348
He knows me.

858
01:14:52,675 --> 01:14:54,586
He knows the demands of my work.

859
01:14:55,155 --> 01:14:56,827
You don't love him.

860
01:14:57,995 --> 01:14:59,508
He and I are the same.

861
01:15:02,035 --> 01:15:03,388
And I want that.

862
01:15:06,995 --> 01:15:10,670
And I want somebody who can
feel my hand when I touch him.

863
01:15:12,355 --> 01:15:13,913
But you can feel me.

864
01:15:14,195 --> 01:15:15,787
You felt me.

865
01:15:17,475 --> 01:15:19,113
I want to say goodbye.

866
01:15:21,315 --> 01:15:22,987
I don't want to see you again.

867
01:19:14,635 --> 01:19:15,954
Hey, buddy.

868
01:19:16,915 --> 01:19:18,314
You can't be in here.

869
01:19:19,155 --> 01:19:20,110
Do you see me?

870
01:19:21,955 --> 01:19:23,434
Do you see me?

871
01:19:23,875 --> 01:19:25,194
Can you see me?

872
01:19:25,515 --> 01:19:26,584
We can see you.

873
01:19:28,475 --> 01:19:29,828
Is this blood?

874
01:19:30,115 --> 01:19:30,945
This is blood!

875
01:19:31,355 --> 01:19:32,470
Is it red?

876
01:19:32,995 --> 01:19:33,871
Red?

877
01:19:34,315 --> 01:19:35,464
Is it red?

878
01:19:36,835 --> 01:19:38,234
Color.

879
01:19:38,555 --> 01:19:40,511
What color were the drugs you took?

880
01:19:41,795 --> 01:19:43,069
Better get your butt out of here.

881
01:19:43,955 --> 01:19:45,024
You got somewhere to go?

882
01:19:48,835 --> 01:19:49,984
Maggie.

883
01:20:01,715 --> 01:20:04,434
Down and down and down I go

884
01:20:04,715 --> 01:20:06,831
Round and round and round I go

885
01:20:07,555 --> 01:20:09,113
Round and spin

886
01:20:09,395 --> 01:20:11,431
Loving the spin I'm in

887
01:20:11,755 --> 01:20:14,144
Loving that old black magic...

888
01:20:14,435 --> 01:20:16,312
...called love

889
01:20:17,755 --> 01:20:19,552
Love!

890
01:20:20,835 --> 01:20:21,950
Hi!

891
01:20:31,515 --> 01:20:34,712
I was wondering if you could tell me
how to get to the county hospital?

892
01:21:17,035 --> 01:21:18,150
Can I help you, sir?

893
01:21:18,395 --> 01:21:21,068
I'll just take a moment
to catch my breath.

894
01:21:22,075 --> 01:21:22,871
Breath!

895
01:21:26,235 --> 01:21:27,224
Maggie Rice.

896
01:21:28,915 --> 01:21:30,030
Are you a patient?

897
01:21:30,435 --> 01:21:31,948
No. I just need to find her, please.

898
01:21:32,355 --> 01:21:34,585
You'll have to call her office.
Someone there can help you.

899
01:21:35,235 --> 01:21:36,384
Do you know where she is?

900
01:21:37,155 --> 01:21:38,986
No, sir, I do not know where she is.

901
01:21:42,235 --> 01:21:43,793
You have this computer...

902
01:21:45,115 --> 01:21:47,071
...and all this technology.
Can't you look her up?

903
01:21:50,795 --> 01:21:51,944
Where's Maggie?

904
01:21:57,115 --> 01:21:58,707
So you're a friend of Maggie's?

905
01:22:00,795 --> 01:22:01,989
What happened to you?

906
01:22:02,315 --> 01:22:03,225
Sorry.

907
01:22:03,675 --> 01:22:04,744
It's okay.

908
01:22:07,755 --> 01:22:08,904
I fell.

909
01:22:09,395 --> 01:22:11,955
Evidently. Off a train?

910
01:22:12,875 --> 01:22:14,388
I fell in love.

911
01:22:21,475 --> 01:22:22,988
Please help me find her.

912
01:22:27,995 --> 01:22:31,192
She went to Lake Tahoe. Her uncle
has a cabin on the Nevada side.

913
01:22:31,515 --> 01:22:32,470
Wait!

914
01:23:02,795 --> 01:23:03,944
Cassiel.

915
01:23:04,875 --> 01:23:06,024
Are you there?

916
01:23:14,675 --> 01:23:15,551
Hello.

917
01:24:08,515 --> 01:24:09,709
Where you headed?

918
01:24:11,355 --> 01:24:12,185
Tahoe!

919
01:24:13,555 --> 01:24:14,704
Reno!

920
01:24:15,035 --> 01:24:16,070
Tahoe!

921
01:24:16,715 --> 01:24:17,989
I'm going to Reno.

922
01:24:18,355 --> 01:24:19,708
I'm going to Tahoe.

923
01:24:20,235 --> 01:24:22,544
Hop in. We'll figure it out
when we get there.

924
01:26:34,195 --> 01:26:35,674
Am I too late?

925
01:26:37,355 --> 01:26:38,310
Too late?

926
01:26:39,195 --> 01:26:40,264
Jordan?

927
01:26:44,515 --> 01:26:46,187
I couldn't marry Jordan.

928
01:26:49,395 --> 01:26:50,987
I'm in love with you.

929
01:26:58,835 --> 01:27:00,109
What happened?

930
01:27:03,435 --> 01:27:04,754
Free will.

931
01:27:19,315 --> 01:27:20,748
I feel you.

932
01:28:36,595 --> 01:28:37,994
Do you feel that?

933
01:28:38,355 --> 01:28:39,390
Yes.

934
01:28:41,315 --> 01:28:42,543
And that?

935
01:28:46,475 --> 01:28:49,148
How's it feel?
Tell me what it feels like.

936
01:28:50,155 --> 01:28:51,429
I can't.

937
01:28:53,395 --> 01:28:54,305
Try.

938
01:28:56,115 --> 01:28:57,230
Warm.

939
01:29:02,475 --> 01:29:03,703
Aching.

940
01:29:21,115 --> 01:29:22,309
It's okay.

941
01:29:25,035 --> 01:29:26,150
We fit together.

942
01:29:26,515 --> 01:29:27,470
I know.

943
01:29:28,235 --> 01:29:30,191
We were made to fit together.

944
01:29:50,875 --> 01:29:53,753
I always asked the dying what
they liked best about living.

945
01:29:56,355 --> 01:29:58,027
Wrote it down in my book.

946
01:30:00,475 --> 01:30:01,590
This is it.

947
01:30:03,155 --> 01:30:04,793
This is what I like best.

948
01:30:05,755 --> 01:30:07,791
You haven't even started yet.

949
01:30:08,555 --> 01:30:10,864
We have our whole lives together.

950
01:30:11,195 --> 01:30:12,344
You and me.

951
01:30:12,595 --> 01:30:14,472
Mr. and Mrs. Plate.

952
01:35:37,235 --> 01:35:39,112
-I'll get help.
-You're here.

953
01:35:39,795 --> 01:35:41,228
-Stay.
-I should get help.

954
01:35:41,475 --> 01:35:43,431
Don't go. The driver went.

955
01:35:43,675 --> 01:35:44,903
Please stay.

956
01:35:45,235 --> 01:35:47,032
Please stay with me.

957
01:35:47,795 --> 01:35:49,194
I'm scared.

958
01:35:53,715 --> 01:35:55,148
I screwed up.

959
01:35:56,515 --> 01:35:58,312
I wanted to show you everything.

960
01:35:58,755 --> 01:35:59,904
You will.

961
01:36:03,435 --> 01:36:06,029
You came all this way.

962
01:36:07,355 --> 01:36:08,788
I'm sorry.

963
01:36:09,835 --> 01:36:11,712
God, no, Maggie!

964
01:36:12,755 --> 01:36:14,029
To touch you...

965
01:36:14,275 --> 01:36:15,424
...and to feel you.

966
01:36:16,315 --> 01:36:19,193
To be able to hold your hand right now.

967
01:36:19,595 --> 01:36:20,710
You know what that means?

968
01:36:20,955 --> 01:36:23,515
Do you know how much I love you?

969
01:36:27,875 --> 01:36:29,866
Keep looking at me, okay?

970
01:36:31,435 --> 01:36:33,107
Look right in my eyes.

971
01:36:34,995 --> 01:36:36,633
Someone's out there.

972
01:36:38,555 --> 01:36:41,831
Don't look at them.
Please don't you look at them!

973
01:36:42,075 --> 01:36:43,554
Is this what happens?

974
01:36:50,395 --> 01:36:51,350
Yes.

975
01:36:57,595 --> 01:36:59,233
This is what happens.

976
01:37:03,515 --> 01:37:05,233
I'm not afraid.

977
01:37:09,155 --> 01:37:10,747
When they ask me...

978
01:37:12,755 --> 01:37:14,074
...what I liked the best...

979
01:37:16,315 --> 01:37:17,430
...I'll tell them...

980
01:37:17,755 --> 01:37:19,154
...it was you.

981
01:37:48,075 --> 01:37:49,110
God!

982
01:39:47,635 --> 01:39:50,024
I can't see you,
but I know you're there.

983
01:39:52,475 --> 01:39:53,590
I'm sorry.

984
01:39:57,235 --> 01:39:58,384
Get out.

985
01:40:00,915 --> 01:40:03,383
Was it you? Were you the one?
Were you there?

986
01:40:03,955 --> 01:40:04,831
No.

987
01:40:06,035 --> 01:40:07,184
Why did He do this?

988
01:40:07,475 --> 01:40:08,430
I don't know.

989
01:40:08,675 --> 01:40:09,790
Because her number was up?

990
01:40:10,955 --> 01:40:12,513
What do you want me to say?

991
01:40:19,955 --> 01:40:22,992
-Am I being punished?
-You know better than that.

992
01:40:24,595 --> 01:40:26,153
That's life.

993
01:40:27,875 --> 01:40:28,990
You're living now.

994
01:40:30,835 --> 01:40:31,790
And one day...

995
01:40:32,435 --> 01:40:33,709
...you'll be dying.

996
01:40:40,235 --> 01:40:41,224
What's it like?

997
01:40:42,515 --> 01:40:43,391
What?

998
01:40:44,475 --> 01:40:45,430
Warmth.

999
01:40:47,635 --> 01:40:48,954
It's wonderful.

1000
01:40:50,995 --> 01:40:53,065
If you'd known this was going to happen...

1001
01:40:54,715 --> 01:40:55,943
...would you have done it?

1002
01:41:01,835 --> 01:41:03,712
I would rather have had...

1003
01:41:05,395 --> 01:41:07,192
...one breath of her hair...

1004
01:41:10,795 --> 01:41:12,513
...one kiss of her mouth...

1005
01:41:15,475 --> 01:41:17,431
...one touch of her hand...

1006
01:41:19,555 --> 01:41:21,625
...than an eternity without it.

1007
01:41:24,595 --> 01:41:25,584
One.

1008
01:49:32,355 --> 01:49:33,344
Subtitled by:
GELULA & CO., INC.

